title: HS Roundup: Horseheads stays unbeaten in volleyball
text:
HS Roundup: Horseheads stays unbeaten in volleyball Andrew Legare, alegare@stargazette.com | @SGAndrewLegare 10:32 p.m. EDT October 20, 2015 Megyan Merrill and Emily Crowell had eight kills each as the Blue Raiders swept Corning Multisport logo. CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Megyan Merrill and Emily Crowell had eight kills each as the Horseheads girls volleyball team remained unbeaten with a 25-11, 25-13, 25-19 victory over visiting Southern Tier Athletic Conference opponent Corning on Tuesday. 
Paige Standish added 28 setter assists for Horseheads (13-0). Emily Smith contributed 11 digs and six aces. 
"The girls played well. They served tough," Horseheads head coach Patti Perone said. "They were hitting tough. Corning dug up some amazing balls. I thought they did a real nice job. They just seemed to struggle with serve receive tonight." 
Ashlyn Amsden had five aces for Corning. 
Union-Endicott 3, Elmira 1 : Kate Brennan had 17 kills and Emmalyn LaPier added 16 kills as Union-Endicott (8-7) topped host Elmira, 24-26, 25-14, 25-15, 25-16 in a STAC match. 
Braeden Knoll had eight kills and seven digs for the Express (0-15). Danielle Dille added 12 assists, Claire Murphy contributed seven blocks and six kills, and Jessica Grogan had 10 digs. 
Watkins Glen 3, Dryden 0 : Amanda Pike had 11 kills and eight digs to help Interscholastic Athletic Conference South Large School champion Watkins Glen sweep host Dryden, 27-25, 25-16, 25-19. 
Girls soccer 
Bainbridge-Guilford 2, Odessa-Montour 0 : At Odessa, goals from Cassidy Graham and Brittany Spake helped 12th-seeded Bainbridge-Guilford to a victory over fifth-seeded Odessa-Montour in the first round of the Section 4 Class C tournament. 
O-M finished with a 12-5 record that included the IAC Small School title. 
Susquehanna Valley 3, Waverly 0 : At Susquehanna Valley, Torriana Graham and Hannah Haskell each had a goal and an assist to help the third-seeded Sabers beat sixth-seeded Waverly in a Section 4 Class B quarterfinal. 
Zoe Mennig had six saves for Waverly, which finished with an 8-5-1 record. 
Girls swimming 
Notre Dame 94, Elmira 87 : Catherine Craig, Molly Craig and Frances VanderMeer each won two individual events and contributed to two relay victories as Elmira Notre Dame topped Elmira in a non-league meet. 
Catherine Craig won the 200-yard freestyle (2:08.94) and 100 butterfly (1:08.07), Molly Craig won the 200 individual medley (2:15.86) and 500 freestyle (5:16.72), and VanderMeer won the 50 freestyle (25.52) and 100 freestyle (55.80).
